# Session Creation and Storage

Based on the codebase, here's what happens during session creation and what is stored:

## Session Creation Flow

Session creation occurs in **`src/auth/auth.service.ts`** during the login process:

```typescript
// In validateLogin() method (line ~70)
const hash = crypto
  .createHash('sha256')
  .update(randomStringGenerator())
  .digest('hex');

const session = await this.sessionService.create({
  user,
  hash,
});
```

## What Gets Stored

The session stores three main pieces of data:

### 1. **Session Entity/Schema Structure**

**Relational (PostgreSQL)** - `src/session/infrastructure/persistence/relational/entities/session.entity.ts`:
```typescript
@Entity({ name: 'session' })
export class SessionEntity extends EntityRelationalHelper {
  @PrimaryGeneratedColumn()
  id: number;                    // Auto-generated session ID

  @ManyToOne(() => UserEntity, { eager: true })
  @Index()
  user: UserEntity;              // Reference to the user

  @Column()
  hash: string;                  // Cryptographic hash (SHA256)

  @CreateDateColumn()
  createdAt: Date;               // Creation timestamp

  @UpdateDateColumn()
  updatedAt: Date;               // Last update timestamp

  @DeleteDateColumn()
  deletedAt: Date;               // Soft delete timestamp
}
```

**Document (MongoDB)** - `src/session/infrastructure/persistence/document/entities/session.schema.ts`:
```typescript
@Schema({ timestamps: true })
export class SessionSchemaClass extends EntityDocumentHelper {
  @Prop({ type: mongoose.Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'UserSchemaClass' })
  user: string;                  // Reference to user ID

  @Prop()
  hash: string;                  // Cryptographic hash

  @Prop({ default: now })
  createdAt: Date;

  @Prop({ default: now })
  updatedAt: Date;

  @Prop()
  deletedAt: Date;
}
```

## Session Usage in JWT Tokens

The session information is embedded in the JWT token payload (**`src/auth/strategies/types/jwt-payload.type.ts`**):

```typescript
export type JwtPayloadType = Pick<User, 'id' | 'role'> & {
  sessionId: Session['id'];      // Session ID stored in JWT
  iat: number;                   // Issued at
  exp: number;                   // Expiration
};
```

## Key Operations

### Token Refresh with Session Hash Update
In **`src/auth/auth.service.ts`** `refreshToken()` method:
```typescript
const hash = crypto
  .createHash('sha256')
  .update(randomStringGenerator())
  .digest('hex');

const session = await this.sessionService.updateByHash(
  { id: data.sessionId, hash: data.hash },  // Verify old hash
  { hash },                                   // Update with new hash
);
```

This implements **hash rotation** on each refresh to invalidate old tokens.

### Session Cleanup
Sessions can be deleted in several ways (**`src/session/infrastructure/persistence/relational/repositories/session.repository.ts`**):

```typescript
deleteById(id)                           // Delete specific session
deleteByUserId({ userId })              // Delete all user sessions
deleteByUserIdWithExclude({...})         // Delete all except one (when changing password)
```

## Summary

| Field | Purpose | Storage |
|-------|---------|---------|
| `id` | Primary key | Auto-generated |
| `user` | User reference | FK to users table |
| `hash` | Security token | SHA256 hash, rotates on refresh |
| `createdAt` | Audit | Auto-generated |
| `updatedAt` | Audit | Auto-generated |
| `deletedAt` | Soft delete | Manual set on logout |

The session design enables **secure token refresh** with hash rotation, **logout capability**, and **concurrent session management** per user.
